    • Constructor Detail

      • GVRCylinderSceneObject

        public GVRCylinderSceneObject(GVRContext gvrContext,
                              GVRCylinderSceneObject.CylinderParams params)
        Constructs a cylinder scene object based on a set of parameters. Height height of cylinder (default 1). TopRadius radius of cylinder top (default 0.5). BottomRadius radius of cylinder bottom (default 0.5). StackNumber number of stacks in cylinder body (default 10). SliceNumber number of slices in cylinder caps (default 36). FacingOut true for normals facing out, false for normals facing in (default true). HasTopCap true to include top cap, false to omit it (default true). HasBottomCap true to include bottom cap, false to omit it (default true). Material GVRMaterial to apply to cylinder (default null).
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - current GVRContext
        params - CylinderParams object with cylinder construction parameters.

      • GVRCylinderSceneObject

        public GVRCylinderSceneObject(GVRContext gvrContext)
        Constructs a cylinder scene object with a height of 1, radius of 0.5, 10 stacks, and 36 slices. The cylinder's triangles and normals are facing out and the same texture will be applied to top, bottom, and side of the cylinder.
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - current GVRContext

      • GVRCylinderSceneObject

        public GVRCylinderSceneObject(GVRContext gvrContext,
                              boolean facingOut)
        Constructs a cylinder scene object with a height of 1, radius of 0.5, 10 stacks, and 36 slices. The cylinder's triangles and normals are facing either in or out and the same texture will be applied to top, bottom, and side of the cylinder.
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - current GVRContext
        facingOut - whether the triangles and normals should be facing in or facing out.

      • GVRCylinderSceneObject

        public GVRCylinderSceneObject(GVRContext gvrContext,
                              boolean facingOut,
                              java.util.ArrayList<java.util.concurrent.Future<GVRTexture>> futureTextureList)
        Constructs a cylinder scene object with a height of 1, radius of 0.5, 10 stacks, and 36 slices. The cylinder's triangles and normals are facing either in or out. The top, bottom, and side of the cylinder each has its own texture.
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - current GVRContext
        facingOut - whether the triangles and normals should be facing in or facing out.
        futureTextureList - the list of three textures for the cylinder. Future<GVRTexture> is used here for asynchronously loading the texture. The six textures are for top, side, and bottom faces respectively.

        Constructs a cylinder scene object with user-specified height, top-radius, bottom-radius, stacks, slices. The cylinder's triangles and normals are facing either in or out and the same material will be applied to top, bottom, and side of the cylinder.

        topRadius - radius for the top of the cylinder
        height - height of the cylinder
        stackNumber - number of quads high to make the cylinder.
        sliceNumber - number of quads around to make the cylinder.
        facingOut - true for normals facing out, false for normals facing in.

      • GVRCylinderSceneObject

        public GVRCylinderSceneObject(GVRContext gvrContext,
                              float bottomRadius,
                              float topRadius,
                              float height,
                              int stackNumber,
                              int sliceNumber,
                              boolean facingOut,
                              java.util.ArrayList<java.util.concurrent.Future<GVRTexture>> futureTextureList,
                              int stackSegmentNumber,
                              int sliceSegmentNumber)
        Constructs a cylinder scene object with user-specified height, top-radius, bottom-radius, stacks, slices. The sphere is subdivided into MxN meshes, where M=sliceSegmengNumber and N=(stackSegmentNumber+2) are specified by user. The cylinder's triangles and normals are facing either in or out. The top, bottom, and side of the cylinder each has its own texture.
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - current GVRContext
        bottomRadius - radius for the bottom of the cylinder
        topRadius - radius for the top of the cylinder
        height - height of the cylinder
        stackNumber - number of quads high to make the cylinder.
        sliceNumber - number of quads around to make the cylinder.
        futureTextureList - the list of three textures for the cylinder. Future< {@code GVRTexture}> is used here for asynchronously loading the texture. The six textures are for top, side, and bottom faces respectively.
        stackSegmentNumber - the segment number along vertical direction (i.e. stacks). Note only body is subdivided along vertical direction. Number of stacks (i.e. stackNumber) should be divisible by stackSegmentNumber.
        sliceSegmentNumber - the segment number along horizontal direction (i.e. slices). Number of slices (i.e. sliceNumber) should be divisible by sliceSegmentNumber.
        facingOut - true for normals facing out, false for normals facing in.

      • GVRCylinderSceneObject

        public GVRCylinderSceneObject(GVRContext gvrContext,
                              float bottomRadius,
                              float topRadius,
                              float height,
                              int stackNumber,
                              int sliceNumber,
                              boolean facingOut,
                              GVRMaterial material,
                              int stackSegmentNumber,
                              int sliceSegmentNumber)
        Constructs a cylinder scene object with user-specified height, top-radius, bottom-radius, stacks, slices. The sphere is subdivided into MxN meshes, where M=sliceSegmengNumber and N=(stackSegmentNumber+2) are specified by user. The cylinder's triangles and normals are facing either in or out and the same material will be applied to top, bottom, and side of the cylinder.
        Parameters:
        gvrContext - current GVRContext
        bottomRadius - radius for the bottom of the cylinder
        topRadius - radius for the top of the cylinder
        height - height of the cylinder
        stackNumber - number of quads high to make the cylinder.
        sliceNumber - number of quads around to make the cylinder.
        material - the material for the cylinder.
        stackSegmentNumber - the segment number along vertical direction (i.e. stacks). Note only body is subdivided along vertical direction. Number of stacks (i.e. stackNumber) should be divisible by stackSegmentNumber.
        sliceSegmentNumber - the segment number along horizontal direction (i.e. slices). Number of slices (i.e. sliceNumber) should be divisible by sliceSegmentNumber.
        facingOut - true for normals facing out, false for normals facing in.
